args: (Found themâ€”blueprints for a command\nunit and for a mass-production unit!)
(All I have to do is read these, and\nthen I can determine if it's possible\nfor me to give my heart to Finni.)
(I'd like to analyze them right away, but\nfirst I need to prioritize downloading the\ndata. I can't tarry here too long.)
Attention: this is a notice from the\nHumanoid Liberation Agency.

A dragon signature has been confirmed
in the vicinity of this base. All functional
units are to re-equip with anti-dragon
armaments and report to point 246.
(What?! A sortie order now, of all times?)
(I'll attract suspicion if I don't comply...but\nI'm not done with the data transfer yet!)
(Hrk... I've got to buy more time.)
Abnormality detected in leg joint.\nRequesting re-servicing.
(I have to get the blueprints while I still\ncan! Data transfer at 70 percent... 80...)
If impairment is minor, requesting that\nunit proceed with the operation. Scanning\nunit to determine level of abnormality.
No abnormality with leg joint detected.\nFurther...

Mismatch detected between exterior
components and internal construction.
Unit in question is a command unit...
Designation Eirene.
No! She's seen through my camouflage!
Blueprint data transfer at 100 percent!\nThat's one objective done for now!
Terminating maverick unit. All units, adjust\ntarget from dragon to defector unit Eirene.
Commencing combat simulation...\nObjective is to escape from the base.
Order to all units: pursue unit Eirene.
Reinforced armor equipped.\nConnecting circuits.\nAll systems normal.
I didn't want to fight any of my fellow\nandroids, but it looks as though I have\nno other choice.
Battle complete. That should've\nbeen the last of my pursuers.
But my sensors are picking up a number\nof signatures. A huge force of androids is\ndeploying from the base.
That being said, I have put quite some\ndistance between us. I should be able\nto escape the high-alert area.
Activating sensor. Commencing search for\nhostile signatures at maximum radius.
...All right. I think I'm in the clear.
I feared the worst when Anassa saw\nthrough my deception. What a relief.
Now to pore over the blueprint data.
Analyzing basic internal construction...\nAnalyzing control system functions...
Analyzing design for compatibility between\ncommand and mass-production units...\nAnalysis complete.
I finally have an answer to whether\nor not I can give my heart to Finni.
